uing on his Grand Prix tour to Japan. He first arrived at the PSS Mutiara Damansara where he spent about 15 minutes interacting with the customers. Following this, he arrived at the PSS Taman Tun Dr Ismail, where he was surrounded by fans the moment he stepped in.One of the customers, Syed Hashim Omar Aljunid said, “I was really surprised! It was definitely a good kind of surprise – to have a Formula One world championship driver fuel up my car. For me, it is a big honour.”Another unsuspecting customer Mohd Arif Abu Bakar was equally surprised. “I just bought my brand new car and the PETRONAS station was my first stop to tank-up with PETRONAS PRIMAX 95 XTRA. I really did not expect to see a Formula One driver here, what more to tank up my new car. It was definitely a double joy for me – a day that I will cherish for a long time.”Indeed, at PETRONAS service stations, it is more than just fuelling vehicles. It is a one-stop centre that comes with shopping, banking, dining, on-going rewards and now, with a possibility of having a Formula One driver fuel up for you! Moving forward, PDB is committed to bring more such unique fuelling experiences to its valued customers.To know what is coming up next, logon to www.mymesra.com.my or join us as a fan at www.facebook.com/petronasbrands.ABOUT PETRONAS DAGANGAN BERHADPETRONAS Dagangan Berhad is the principal domestic marketing arm of Petroliam Nasional Berhad (PETRONAS), the national oil company, which holds 69.86% of its equity. The Company markets a wide range of high quality petroleum products including motor gasoline, aviation fuel, kerosene, diesel, fuel oil, bunker fuel, lubricants, liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) and asphalt in Malaysia. For media enquiries, please contact: PETRONAS Dagangan BerhadIzrin Muhayi MsTel       : 03 – 2331 6837Fax      : 03 – 2331 6882Email   : izrinm@petronas.com.my Or Perspective Strategies Sdn BhdAnupama Arvind, MsTel       : 03 – 7987 2372Fax      : 03 – 7987 2373Email   : anupama.arvind@perspective.com.my Lim Hwee Nee, MsTel       : 03 – 7987 2372Fax      : 03 – 7987 2373Email   : lim.hwee.nee@perspective.com.my 更多PETRONAS Brands · 2011年10月10日 · PETRONAS XTRA CHALLENGE EYES 300 MOTORISTS DURING SEVEN-LEG SERIES Initiative by PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad to boost product under Petaling Jaya, 1 October 2011 – As part of its efforts to further boost product understanding and appreciation, PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad (PDB) kick-started the next phase of the PETRONAS PRIMAX 95 Xtra campaign with the PETRONAS XTRA Challenge targeting 300 customers nationwide over the three-month period. The first l⋯⋯繼續閱讀PETRONAS Brands · 2011年9月4日 · “MY RAYA MOMENTS AT PETRONAS STATION” VIDEO CONTEST - HOW TO PARTICIPATE & TERMS AND CONDITIONS “MY RAYA MOMENTS AT PETRONAS STATION” VIDEO CONTEST How to participate: ⋯⋯繼續閱讀PETRONAS Brands · 2011年6月20日 · PETRONAS DAGANGAN CROWNS VIRTUAL RACE KING PETALING JAYA, 17 June 2011 – PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad (PDB) today crowned Paul Tan, Founder and Blogger of Paul Tan Automotive News, the Racing King of the PETRONAS PRIMAX 95 XTRA Race at the Appreciation Party, which saw about 100 of Paul Tan’s supporters joining in the fun and celebration along with race rivals celebrity Juliana Evans and Hitz ⋯⋯FM DJ Ean. The PETRONAS PRIMAX 95 XTRA Race is a virtual race organised recently through Petronasbrands Facebook Fanpage. Starting 3 May, fans were called to virtually ‘fuel’ their favourite racer with PRIMAX 95 XTRA to the finish line. Fans who supported the winner throughout the race then stood a chance to be invited to the exclusive PETRONAS PRIMAX 95 XTRA Race Appreciation Party. During the event, Ir Izuddin Husaini, Senior General Manager of Retail Business Division who hosted the party on behalf of PDB, said, “While we celebrate Paul Tan’s victory, we also want to show our appreciation to our racers and fans who have supported the PETRONAS PRIMAX 95 XTRA race. It is also through this platform that we hope to build the mindshare of PETRONAS PRIMAX 95 XTRA with fellow car enthusiasts.” “We are indeed delighted to be able to meet some of the fans in person this evening. PDB appreciates the fact that these fans are also PETRONAS ambassadors as they talk about their experience with friends and also provide us with valuable feedback on our products and services,” he added. Throughout the race, Paul Tan, Juliana and Ean took to Facebook, Twitter and Blogs to call for support. What started as a close competition soon saw Paul Tan leading the race towards the end, thanks to his large group of ‘motoring’ fans who diligently ‘pumped’ his virtual car with PETRONAS PRIMAX 95 XTRA. Paul Tan triumphed with close to 500 while Juliana followed closely behind with 418 supporters.  In the presence of enthusiastic party revelers, Izuddin presented the Winner’s Trophy to Paul Tan and a token of appreciation consisting of PETRONAS PRIMAX 95 XTRA merchandises, PETRONAS Gift Card and Formula One Touch n’ Go card. Both Juliana and Ean were also presented with trophies and tokens of appreciation. Elaborating further on what is in store for its customers, Izuddin said, “We are committed to introduce products which are as innovative as our PRIMAX 95 XTRA fuel, if not more. We will also continue to roll out a variety of exciting contests with more great prizes and rewards in the future.” Since the launch on 9 April 2011, PETRONAS PRIMAX 95 XTRA has lived up to its association to Formula 1™ technology by delivering superior power coupled with more kilometre per litre. Visibly enjoying each moment of the party and his win, the prominent blogger said, “The PETRONAS PRIMAX 95 XTRA Race has been great fun and I’m indeed delighted to be part of this race. I guess there is no need for me to elaborate on the tremendous support and response received from the fans throughout the race”. Guests were treated to a scrumptious dinner laid-out for the crowd followed by exciting trivia challenges and racing games conducted on Playstations and iPads befitting the Formula One-inspired theme of the PETRONAS PRIMAX 95 XTRA Race Appreciation Party.    For more exciting events, logon to www.facebook.com/petronasbrands or www.mymesra.com.my.  更多PETRONAS Brands · 2011年6月16日 · PETRONAS DAGANGAN REWARDS 153 LUCKY CUSTOMERS KUALA LUMPUR, 14 June 2011 – As part of its ongoing commitment to recognise and reward loyal customers, PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad (PDB) today rewarded 153 lucky winners of the PETRONAS The Road to Rewards – Kedai Mesra campaign with exciting prizes worth RM200,000, amidst much fanfare and celebrations. ⋯⋯The two-month long campaign drew 450,000 customers nationwide, of which 150 were selected as Monthly Winners while additional three lucky customers were crowned Special Winners. Participation in the campaign was made easy requiring the customers to only purchase any two items from the participating brands available at more than 600 Kedai Mesra nationwide.  At the prize giving ceremony, Ir. Izuddin Husaini Mohd Yusoff, Senior General Manager of Retail Business Division said, “Given our ongoing efforts to recognise and reward our customers, we have established the PETRONAS Road to Rewards as a pivotal campaign to provide exclusive privileges and benefits to our valued customers.” “Over the years, PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad has organised many customer outreach and marketing promotions aimed at building and retaining our customers nationwide. We will continue to push the bar on product innovation and service excellence,” he added. The crowd cheered enthusiastically as the Grand Prize winner walked away with a Travel Voucher worth RM20,000 and a cash prize worth RM10,000. Additionally, the First Prize winner received a Travel Voucher worth RM15,000 and a cash prize of RM5,000, with the Second Prize winner taking home a Travel Voucher worth RM10,000 and a cash prize worth RM3,000. All three special winners were also presented with a Nikon DSLR D90 camera and 500,000 PETRONAS Mesra Card points each. Meanwhile, the monthly winners received numerous prizes such as the PETRONAS gift cards worth RM500, 50,000 Mesra Card points, Canon EOS550D camera, Alienware M11X Laptop and Smart Tag with Limited Edition PETRONAS Touch & Go Card worth RM100. Elaborating further on the various efforts undertaken by PDB towards enhancing customers’ experience, Izuddin said, “For us, putting our customers’ best interest first is a priority. We want customers to be assured of the best convenience when fuelling up their vehicles, knowing that a wide range of services and offerings are available within our one-stop centre.” “Moving forward, we will continue to offer more reward-based programmes to enable everyone to enjoy the privileges of being a PETRONAS customer,” he added.  Apart from rewarding their loyal customers, PETRONAS The Road to Rewards – Kedai Mesra also aimed at increasing the awareness of the convenience offered at PETRONAS stations. Customers can shop at its Kedai Mesra as well as enjoy the ease of using other services available there including ATMs, Touch n Go, e-pay, bill payment and even purchasing bus tickets. Quick Serve Restaurants and other refreshments are also available at selected stations. Moreover, earlier this year, PDB organised the Road to Rewards ‘Ride the RM3 million Wave’ campaign that rewarded RM3 million worth of prizes to its loyal customers. Over and above this, the Company also held the PETRONAS Fuel-up promotion recently during which winners were presented with a total of 20 Apple iPads. Enjoying the festivities at the event, grand prize winner, Nurzila Binti Yusuf from Kedah, appeared delighted at her lucky win. “Even on days when I don’t fuel up my car, I would still stop by at PETRONAS Stations to do my banking and stock up some snacks. Now on top of that, I won such great prizes just by shopping at Kedai Mesra. Who doesn’t love to get paid for shopping?” she beamed. Also visibility elated at his good fortune was the second prize winner Mohd Shazwan Hafiz Bin Mohd Shukri, a student of Universiti Teknologi MARA (UiTM), remarked that he could now fulfil his long time wish of taking his parents on a holiday. Tucking into the scrumptious lunch laid out for the winners and guests, Hafiz said, “It’s been awhile since we had a family holiday together. The travel voucher will definitely come in handy. This vacation will also be a nice time for me to start on my photography hobby, now that I have a good camera to snap around with.”   The participating brands in the PETRONAS The Road to Rewards – Kedai Mesra campaign include PDB’s retail business partners such as Tropicana Twister, Spritzer Tinge, Red Bull, 100 Plus, Dutch Lady, Nescafe, Ribena and F&N Seasons. For updates on forthcoming campaigns and exciting offers, please visit www.mymesra.com.my 更多PETRONAS Brands · 2011年4月11日 · PB Winners Get Exclusive Paddock and Garage VisitsIt was not just luck but pure effort that five PETRONAS Brands FB fans, who submitted creative pictures of themselves as Formula One drivers, were selected as the winners of the Formula One PRIMAX Power contest. Each won the coveted Diamond Grand Stand tickets to watch the Formula One race at Sepang on 9 – 10 April 201, and luckily enough, they cou⋯⋯ld bring a friend with them. While anyone could have purchased tickets to watch the race, it was the extremely exclusive paddock and garage visits that set this winning package apart. Over at the paddock and garage area, the winners witnessed the detailed work and extreme dedication that was involved in prepping for the race. Soon enough, each grew to understand and appreciate how the Formula One technologies behind the cars of Mercedes GP PETRONAS have inspired in the development of the PETRONAS’ latest RON 95 fuel, PRIMAX 95 Xtra. Check out the eleven photo recap that captured the highlights of their visit:             更多PETRONAS Brands · 2011年4月10日 · PDB MD/CEO's Message on PETRONAS PRIMAX 95 XtraGreetings from PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad (PDB)! The 9th of April 2011 marked yet another significant milestone for PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad as we launched an advanced breakthrough fuel- the PRIMAX 95 Xtra. ⋯⋯Our technology team has been hard at work for over two years to develop this fuel, and I am proud to say that they have successfully developed a product proven to provide greater power, smoother acceleration and better fuel mileage as compared to any other equivalent grade product in the market. PDB is proud to bring this innovative creation to you at the same price as that of the regulated price of RON 95 fuel - notwithstanding its superior quality and performance. At PDB, we firmly believe in going all the way to bring the very best of our products and services to our customers. The PRIMAX 95 Xtra is a testimony of our commitment to continuously invest in developing innovative products that meet and exceed our customers’ expectations. The recent launch of the PRIMAX 95 Xtra showcases the importance of continuing research and improvement to the PRIMAX line of products in growing our retail business, as we believe that growth cannot only be in terms of the number of PETRONAS Service Stations we have, but also in continuously improving the quality of our fuel. We have a full-fledged PETRONAS Fuel Technician Team working with our fuel technology partners to continuously innovate and enhance our product offerings. We are excited to bring the F1 technology to the road and share it with all our customers. This is part of PDB’s journey to consistently push the bar on technology to establish a new industry-wide benchmark. Extensive tests have been carried out on the fuel in laboratories and we have carried out road test through our ‘Experience to Believe’ Privileged Trial and the feedback that we have received indicated that the fuel performed better as compared to their current fuel for 90% of the participants. This feedback, coupled with the positive results from independent test centres at Milbrook and Tickford in the UK, has given us the confidence that we certainly have a winning product at hand. Moreover, the launch of “All The Way” is a clear testimony of PDB’s consistent and continuous commitment in developing products and services that exceed consumer and industry expectations. The new PRIMAX 95 Xtra, which is inspired by F1 technology, is one of such efforts to lead the market through innovation. As proven by our consistent track record all through these years, PDB is committed to go ‘All The Way’ to ensure that PETRONAS remains as the Brand of 1st Choice for Malaysians. I’m pleased to inform that you can now join us in this exciting journey on PETRONASBrands Facebook and onyoutube as we go All the Way for you! Amir Hamzah AzizanManaging Director/Chief Executive OfficerPETRONAS Dagangan Berhad 更多PETRONAS Brands · 2011年3月25日 · PETRONAS Formula One Contest's changes on requirements. Please click here for more details.Hi All, we have received some feedback on the contest and made some changes on requirements. Effective now, you have to submit a photo of your Formula One driving expression and write a creative caption with these three words: “Primax”, “Formula One” and “Power” instead of “Primax”, “F1” and “Power”. For those who have submitted previously you don’⋯⋯t have to make any changes. For more details, please view the PETRONAS Formula One tab under our profile picture.What are you waiting for!! Hurry and join the contest now to stand a chance to win a pair of “Diamond” tickets to watch Formula One race at Sepang + Special garage tour + Rain concert (exclusively for Petronasbrands facebook fans). 更多PETRONAS Brands · 2011年3月10日 · Aspiring Chefs from Leading Universities Whip Up Delicacies to Win Cash Prizes Six universities showcased their team’s culinary skills in the inaugural Gas PETRONAS Battle of the Chefs cooking competition and went home with more than RM10,000 worth of cash and prizes. The cooking competition was held on 28 February 2011 at SStwo Mall in Petaling Jaya. It was a gastronomical delight with colourful ingredients and aromatic fla⋯⋯vours of herbs and spices concocted to create dishes that tantalises the taste bud. The clanking sounds of pots and pans and encouraging cheers from friends and supporters filled the SStwo Mall courtyard as the teams battle it out to be dubbed winner of the Gas PETRONAS Battle of the Chefs Cooking Competition. The six universities that took part were Berjaya University College of Hospitality, Universiti Teknologi MARA (UiTM), University Tun Abdul Razak, Universiti Putra Malaysia (UPM), Advanced Management & Technology Centre (PTPL) and Food Institute of Malaysia. Each team comprised three apprentice chefs who were tasked to present their dishes that consisted of an appetizer, a main course and a dessert, all to be prepared and plated within two hours. Judging was based on innovation, taste, presentation, timeliness and hygiene.  The panel of judges were industry’s ‘otai’ – Chef Johari Edrus, former President of Chef Association of Malaysia and Chef Jasman Saidin, former Corporate Executive Chef of Carnival Cruise Liners. Chef Zamzani Abdul Wahab, Malaysia’s celebrity chef who is popularly known as Chef Zam, provided inspiration and words of encouragement to the contestants. The first prize winner went home with RM3,000 cash prize, second prize with RM2,000 cash prize and third prize with RM1,000 cash prize. All three winning teams also received a challenge trophy, exclusive Gas PETRONAS merchandises and 3 cylinders of 14kg Gas PETRONAS cooking gas each. Over and above this, three consolation prizes that consisted of trophies, merchandises and exclusive Gas PETRONAS products were also awarded. The General Manager of PDB’s LPG (liquefied petroleum gas) Business, Zubair Abdul Razak,  said, “As a responsible Malaysian company, PETRONAS Dagangan recognises the importance of playing our part in fostering the development of the local culinary and hospitality industry. The Gas PETRONAS Battle of the Chefs is one of the platforms for us to expose young chefs to competition and to give them an opportunity to further improve the Malaysian hospitality and food-services standards.” We hope this event will motivate our young talents to challenge themselves and craft even better culinary creations, establishing higher benchmarks for other undergraduates to follow, not only in the country but in this region as well, given that Malaysia is striving to become an education hub for this region, he said. List of winners: 1st PrizeFood Institute of Malaysia (FIM)Nurul Azwa Ammeran, Noor Hidayah Aris, Mohd Zulkhairi Zainal Ibidin 2nd PrizeAdvanced Management and Technology Centre (PTPL) 3rd PrizeBerjaya University College of Hospitality Consolation PrizeUniversiti  Tun Abdul RazakUniversiti Teknologi Mara (UiTM)Universiti Putra Malaysia Gas PETRONAS’s True Blue Flame – Cleaner, Hotter and More Economical 更多PETRONAS Brands · 2011年3月3日 · PETRONAS Secured Online Promotion Scam E-Mail!PETRONAS wishes to alert members of the public that the e-mail communications on “PETRONAS Secured Online Promotion” currently circulating on the Internet is a scam devised by unscrupulous individual or parties. The scam e-mail also contains details of a claims officer to be contacted for assistance and disbursement of the alleged cash prize. PETRO⋯⋯NAS wishes to inform that neither PETRONAS nor any subsidiary within its Group of Companies has conducted or authorised such prize redemption schemes and appeals to the public not to respond to the email. This advice also extends to all e-mail or short message service (SMS) communications using PETRONAS’ name in other prize redemption schemes, lucky draws or contests. Issued byReputation ManagementBrand DepartmentPETRONAS Dagangan Berhad 更多更多中文(台灣)English (US)Tiếng ViệtBahasa Indonesiaภาษาไทย日本語EspañolPortuguês (Brasil)Français (France)DeutschItalianoMessengerFacebook Lite用戶地標遊戲地點名人市集社團食譜MomentsInstagram關於刊登廣告建立粉絲專頁開發人員工作機會隱私政策CookieAd Choices使用條